List all available dimensions in the OSPSuite platform

Source: R/utilities-units.R
allAvailableDimensions.Rd

List all available dimensions in the OSPSuite platform

Usage

allAvailableDimensions()

Value

Returns the names of all available dimensions defined in the OSPSuite platform.

Examples


allAvailableDimensions()
#>  [1] "Abundance per mass protein"     "Abundance per tissue"          
#>  [3] "Age in weeks"                   "Age in years"                  
#>  [5] "Amount"                         "Amount per area"               
#>  [7] "Amount per area per time"       "Amount per time"               
#>  [9] "Ampere"                         "Area"                          
#> [11] "AUC (mass)"                     "AUC (molar)"                   
#> [13] "AUCM (molar)"                   "Becquerel"                     
#> [15] "BMI"                            "Candela"                       
#> [17] "CL per mass protein"            "CL per recombinant enzyme"     
#> [19] "Compliance"                     "Compliance (Area)"             
#> [21] "Concentration (mass)"           "Concentration (molar)"         
#> [23] "Concentration (molar) per time" "Coulomb"                       
#> [25] "Count"                          "Count per mass"                
#> [27] "Count per volume"               "CV mmHg*s²/ml"                 
#> [29] "CV Viscosity"                   "CV Viscosity per Volume"       
#> [31] "Density"                        "Diffusion coefficient"         
#> [33] "Dimensionless"                  "Dose per body surface area"
